All plots were created using R library Metadynminer (http://www.metadynamics.cz/metadynminer/).

First set of CVS

library(metadynminer)
h<-read.hills('HILLS_r',ignoretime=T)
## 2D HILLS file read
## Warning: The time will be updated automatically from zero
## according to the first step!
plotheights(h)

f <- fes2(h)
f <- f-min(f)
m <- fesminima(f)
plot(m,zlim=c(0,60))
text(150,28, 'T = 300K',cex=2)

m
##   letter CV1bin CV2bin       CV1        CV2 free_energy
## 1      A     95     20 -45.89184  1.0474901   0.3446691
## 2      B     88    141 -57.16566 16.6393505   2.7640406
## 3      C    105     69 -29.78638  7.3615493  14.1206624
## 4      D     96     51 -44.28129  5.0420990  16.4095679
## 5      E    195     20 115.16279  1.0474901  27.2409359
## 6      F    169     51  73.28858  5.0420990  30.8846797
## 7      G    229     19 169.92136  0.9186318  53.4249889
plot(feprof(m))

Second set of CVS

h2<-read.hills('HILLS_t',ignoretime=T)
## 2D HILLS file read
## Warning: The time will be updated automatically from zero
## according to the first step!
plotheights(h2)

f2 <- fes2(h2)
f2 <- f2-min(f2)
m2 <- fesminima(f2)
plot(m2,zlim=c(0,60))
text(150,120, 'T = 300K',cex=2)

m2
##   letter CV1bin CV2bin        CV1       CV2 free_energy
## 1      A    128    150   8.301233  21.55887    0.000000
## 2      B     94    167 -51.689626  43.38070    7.904527
## 3      C    106    114 -30.516382 -24.65208   10.848882
## 4      D    144    104  36.532226 -37.48846   12.037241
## 5      E     85    121 -67.569560 -15.66662   14.991035
plot(feprof(m2))
